These two chords are 'picked' one string at a time from the A  
string down to the open G. i.e. you pick the three notes in the  
first chord, remove one finger and pick the three notes of the  
second chord (I will refer to this as the 'C Pattern'). This  
pattern is repeated over and over until the line "oh lord how  
quickly, they changed their tune' over which you play (with the  
same 'plucking' pattern as before) - I shall call thi  
  
E|---|---|---|x  
B|---|---|---|x  
G|---|-*-|---|2  
D|---|---|---|x  
A|---|---|-*-|3  
E|-*-|---|---|1  
  
E|---|---|---|x  
B|---|---|---|x  
G|---|---|---|o  
D|---|---|---|x  
A|---|---|-*-|3  
E|-*-|---|---|1  
  
Then change back to the first pattern for the beginning of the  
next piece of lyric. i.e.  
  
